                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conference 861.00/274: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="from"
                            >Wilson</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                            Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">U. S. S. George Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1919</hi>, (?) <hi rend="italic"
                                >a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received in Paris February 20, 11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>W–6. Greatly surprised by <persName corresp="#p_CW1">Churchill</persName>’s
                    Russian suggestion. I distinctly understood <persName corresp="#p_LGD1">Lloyd
                        George</persName> to say that there could be no <pb facs="0184" n="72"
                        xml:id="pg_72"/> thought of military action there and what I said at the
                    hurried meeting Friday afternoon was meant only to convey the idea that I would
                    not take any hasty separate action myself, but would not be in favor of any
                    course [contrary to that which?] may mean the earliest practicable withdrawal of
                    military forces. It would be fatal to be led further into the Russian chaos.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
